headline: Why Robinhood (HOOD) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of financial services company Robinhood (NASDAQ:HOOD) jumped 5.2% in the morning session after the major indices rebounded (Nasdaq +1.5%, S&P 500 +1.0%) as reports pointed to easing tensions between Israel and Iran. The Wall Street Journal said senior Iranian officials had signaled a willingness to restart stalled nuclear talks, on the condition that Washington refrain from joining Israel's ongoing strikes.
